names: The One Who Took Her Away
description: This weekend promised some fantastic functionality in checking off two relatively small red blips left on our maps. Saturday's hit was the most annoying of the two, being a further two-hour drive from Glen Nevis Youth Hostel. We camped the Friday night somewhere iin-between the hostel and the first Munro, in one of the many roadside patches of grass C. Vim had found on Google Maps. It was cold, but some classic Luke Smith content did keep us warm. First time car park camping without the ALL too. What a luxury I'm missing now. Saturday's Munro was good. Nothing in particular stood out, well apart fro meeting the future Craig and Lewis, who decided to recruit us as part of their Loch Mullardoch walk-out fraternity. C. Vim was still pretty ill, so it was a roast chicken in the cards for the hostel storm. We perhaps left this too late however, as its delay did result in a slightly premature blackout from C. Vim. Nothing stopping myself and the dude smashing up some turf though... And nothing stopping the early rise for Sunday's Munro. It was back to the field we'd hit a few weeks prior, this time for Beinn Fhada. All was good until the greasy slab scramble, which led us to some alternative route finding. Sadly this turned the loop into a lollipop loop too. Still got the job done though. Can't say the same about the drive-out with the broken spring on the Volvo, and the Helensburgh detour.
